<TITLE> BAC named </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka , Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)The first sitting of the ninth parliament on Sunday formed the 15-member Business Advisory Committee (BAC), including leader of the House Sheikh Hasina and leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia The other members are Awami League's Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury, Tofail Ahmed, Shawkat Ali, Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim, Suranjit Sengupta, Abdus Shahid, H M Ershad, Rahmat Ali, Rashed Khan Menon, Fazle Rabbi Miah and Abdul Matin Khasru and BNP lawmaker MK Anwar. The BAC, headed by the speaker, fixes the number of working days and agenda ahead of every session. Meanwhile, newly elected speaker Abdul Hamid formed a five-member panel of chairmen. The panel members will preside over sessions in absence of the speaker and the deputy speaker. The panel members are: Ali Ashraf, Fazle Rabbi, Anisul Islam Mahmud, Dhirendra Chandra Debnath and Meher Afroz. bdn
